import re

def pre_process(text):
    
    # lowercase
    text=text.lower()
    
    #remove tags
    text=re.sub("</?.*?>"," <> ",text)
    
    # remove special characters and digits
    text=re.sub("(\\d|\\W|_)+"," ",text)
    
    return text

def get_stop_words(stop_file_path):
    """load stop words """
    
    with open(stop_file_path, 'r', encoding="utf-8") as f:
        stopwords = f.readlines()
        stop_set = set(m.strip() for m in stopwords)
        return frozenset(stop_set)

#load a set of stop words
stopwords=get_stop_words("stopwords.txt")

reviews_all = dat['text'].apply(lambda x:pre_process(x))

5.2 Extract key words for all the reviews¶

In [31]:
topn = 10
results =[]
In [32]:
for idx, doc in reviews_all.items():
    #generate tf-idf for the given document
    tf_idf_vector=reviews_tfidf[idx]
    
    temp = pd.DataFrame(zip(tf_idf_vector.tocoo().col, tf_idf_vector.tocoo().data),columns=['feature_number','tf_idf'])
    temp.sort_values('tf_idf', ascending = False, inplace = True)
    
    #use only topn items from vector
     
    topn_items = temp[:topn]

    tf_idf = []
    word = []

    for index, row in topn_items.iterrows():
        #print(int(row['feature_number']))
        fname = feature_names[int(row['feature_number'])]
        word.append(fname)
        tf_idf.append(round(row['tf_idf'], 3))

    result = dict(zip(word, tf_idf))
    
    results.append(result)

Step 3 – Summarize the findings¶

  • Summarize your work and provide suggestions for further improvements.

We started our analysis by loading the dataset into pandas dataframe and viewing the contents. Then we started text preprocessing in which we got rid of common stop words which has no significance. Then we transformed the data from text to words using bag of words method and tf-idf method. Here we extracted all the keywords in the dataset and gave it weightage based on its frequency and significance. One the keywords were extracted, we moved on to analyzing the keywords using rule based association mining. Here first encoded the dataset using the apriori algorithm and then we tried to find the relationship of each text with one another and how significant each word is in the text. We used the lift and confidence methods to create the relationships. Finally to visualize the dataset we used wordcloud and a barchart to show the frequency and importance of the keywords used in the document.
